                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 E.A.C./9–1644</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 4538</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-16">September 16,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary of State refers to the Department’s telegram No. 6315, August 10, 3
                    p.m., Eacom 29, and encloses herewith a copy of the document (WS–254b) described
                    in paragraph (2) thereof. This document is now awaiting action by the Joint
                    Chiefs of Staff. In the meantime it is being forwarded to the Ambassador for his
                    guidance in as much as it has been cleared by the Department and represents its
                    views with respect to the principal military and political policies to be
                    followed in the administration of Germany.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
